{"id":"6511","name":"Build Using OF Template","tagline":"Build a project and/or task(s) using a Taskpaper template stored in Drafts","icon":"ios13 c2071128575 g59748","latest":"20632","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A simple shortcut that searches Drafts for all the templates that are in there for Omnifocus. It then displays the results from the search and allows selection of one from the list. It will then get the chosen draft and run the “Taskpaper to OF” action on it, this runs the action and places the template’s tasks into Omnifocus.</p>\n<p>In Drafts you will need to create your Omnifocus template in TaskPaper format and save the Draft with two tags: template, omnifocus</p>\n<p>Tip - If there is an Omnifocus project that you want to use multiple times then:\n1. Open the project in Omnifocus\n2. Click on the Sharesheet icon\n3. Select Drafts\nYou now have the Omnifocus project and it’s tasks saved in Drafts in a TaskPaper format. You may want to tidy the text up but ensure you add the tags:\n- template\n- omnifocus</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Sept. 14, 2020, 12:13 p.m.</strong></p>"}